            <entry xml:id="entry_7fson" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ᵆfson</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æfsojnæ</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>повод</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>cause</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>предлог</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>pretext</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>отговорка</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>excuse</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>причина</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>reason</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>су fson?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>почему?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>why?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>me fson æj fækodta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>взвалил (вину) на меня</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he put (the blame) on me</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>rynḱyn æfson yskodta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он притворился больным</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he pretended to be sick</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>saǵy fson xæræg amardta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вместо (под видом) оленя убил осла</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he killed a donkey instead of (disguised as) a deer</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>...afycyn æfsony bajrox wa sæ xærd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>...чтобы (дети) забыли о еде под предлогом, что она (скоро)
                                сварится</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>... so that children forget about food under the pretext that it will
                                soon be cooked</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>46</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Taǵi fembærsta, wazǵyty æfson abyrǵytæ kæj wydysty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Таджи понял, что под видом гостей были разбойники</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Taji realized that there were robbers disguised as guests</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>29</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>kynʒæxsæv k˳y fæcī, wæd padcyx jæxī rynḱyn æfson yskodta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда свадьба кончилась, царь притворился больным</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when the wedding ended, the king pretended to be sick</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>52</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>fyccag syn fækodton æfsony gæræxtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>сперва я сделал по ним ложные (не всерьез) выстрелы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>at first I fired at them fake (not serious) shots</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>176</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Предполагая обычное развитие %ifs%i из %isf%i ← %isp%i,
                    восстанавливаем %i*spāna-%i, чему на %bперсидской%b почве закономерно отвечает
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>sān</w>
                        <gloss><q>способ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>образ</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>вид</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>основание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>причина</q></gloss></mentioned> и пр. (%isān%i относится к
                    %i*spāna-%i, как <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>sag</w>
                        <gloss><q>собака</q></gloss></mentioned> к %i*spaka-%i): <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>či sān ki</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= ос. %iсу
                            fson%i</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= Ossetic %iсу
                            fson%i</note>
                        <gloss><q>почему</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>на каком основании</q></gloss></mentioned>. %bАфг.%b <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>sān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>sān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>sāng</w></mentioned> усвоены из персидского. Дальнейшие связи не ясны.
                    Приняв за семантический стержень понятия ‘вид’, ‘образ’, ‘подобие’, можно
                    отнести сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>afsān</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (← %iaf-sān%i ←
                            %iabi-spāna-%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (← %iaf-sān%i
                            ← %iabi-spāna-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>чародей</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>afsāna</w>
                        <gloss><q>обольщение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>наваждение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>вымысел</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>басня</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>afsūn</w>
                        <gloss><q>чары</q></gloss></mentioned>. Сюда же в этом случае <mentioned
                        xml:lang="gem"><lang/>
                        <w>*span-</w></mentioned> в <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>spanan</w>
                        <gloss><q>обольщать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Gespenst</w>
                        <gloss><q>обольщение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>привидение</q></gloss></mentioned>. И по значению и фонетически
                    напрашивается сближение ос. %ifson%i с <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>sponte</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (творительный
                            падеж)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (instrumental
                            case)</note></mentioned> в таких выражениях, как <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>sponte suā</w>
                        <gloss><q>по собственному побуждению</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>сам по себе</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Suppposing the usual development %ifs%i from %isf%i ← %isp%i, we
                    trace it back to %i*spāna-%i, which regularly corresponds to <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>sān</w>
                        <gloss><q>method</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>way</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>look</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>foundation</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>reason</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. (%isān%i is related to
                    %i*spāna-%i, as <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>sag</w>
                        <gloss><q>dog</q></gloss></mentioned> is related to %i*spaka-%i): <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>či sān ki</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">= ос. %iсу
                            fson%i</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">= Ossetic %iсу
                            fson%i</note>
                        <gloss><q>why</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>on what grounds</q></gloss></mentioned>. <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>sān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/>
                        <w>sān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/>
                        <w>sāng</w></mentioned> were acquired from Persian. The latter relations are
                    unknown. If we take the meaning ‘look’, ‘way’, ‘likeness’ for the semantic
                    foundation, we can also relate the following words to it: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>afsān</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (← %iaf-sān%i ←
                            %iabi-spāna-%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (← %iaf-sān%i
                            ← %iabi-spāna-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>sorcerer</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>afsāna</w>
                        <gloss><q>delusion</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>hallucination</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fantasy</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fable</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                            ><w>afsūn</w>
                        <gloss><q>magic</q></gloss></mentioned>. In this case <mentioned
                        xml:lang="gem"><lang/>
                        <w>*span-</w></mentioned> in <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>spanan</w>
                        <gloss><q>tempt</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Gespenst</w>
                        <gloss><q>temptation</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ghost</q></gloss></mentioned> is also related to it. Both in the
                    meaning and in the phonetic form the relation of Ossetic %ifson%i thrusts itself
                    on <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>sponte</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (творительный
                            падеж)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (instrumental
                            case)</note></mentioned> in such expressions as <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>sponte suā</w>
                        <gloss><q>by one's own will</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>per se</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
            </entry>
